<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Ode to the 18650!</title>
<style>
body {
  font-family: "Comic Sans MS", cursive, sans-serif;
  background-color: #FFFFCC;
  text-align: center;
  margin: 20px;
}

h1 {
  color: #FF0000;
  font-size: 3em;
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #000000;
}

p {
  font-size: 1.2em;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: #000080;
}

.battery-image {
  width: 200px;
  border: 5px ridge #00FF00;
  margin: 20px;
}

.cool-text {
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: bold;
  color: #800080;
}

.ticker-container {
  background-color: #00FFFF;
  overflow: hidden;
  height: 30px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.ticker-text {
  white-space: nowrap;
  animation: ticker 15s linear infinite;
  padding-left: 100%; /* Start offscreen */
}

@keyframes ticker {
  0% { transform: translateX(0); }
  100% { transform: translateX(-100%); }
}

#counter {
  font-size: 2em;
  color: #008000;
  margin-top: 20px;
}

</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>The Glorious 18650 Battery!</h1>

<div class="ticker-container">
  <div class="ticker-text">
    18650! Powering the future! Rechargeable! Reliable! The best battery ever! Get yours today!
  </div>
</div>

<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/18650_lithium_ion_rechargeable_battery.jpg/220px-18650_lithium_ion_rechargeable_battery.jpg" alt="A magnificent 18650 battery" class="battery-image">

<p>Oh, 18650, battery of my dreams!  You power my flashlights, my vapes, and so much more! Your cylindrical majesty is a testament to human ingenuity.</p>

<p>Your <span class="cool-text">energy density</span> is unmatched!  You are a tiny powerhouse, a rechargeable marvel!  I sing your praises!</p>

<p>Without you, where would we be?  Lost in the darkness?  Vaping in the stone age?  The thought is unbearable!</p>

<p>Seriously, though, remember to use them safely!  And always recycle them properly!</p>

<div id="counter">Number of times this page has praised the 18650: <span id="count">0</span></div>

<script>
let count = 0;

function updateCount() {
  count++;
  document.getElementById("count").innerText = count;
}

setInterval(updateCount, 5000); // Increment every 5 seconds, just for fun.

updateCount(); // Initial count
</script>

<hr>
<p>Last updated: May 7, 2024</p>

<img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20090728081732im_/http://geocities.com/wowsohot/undercon.gif" alt="Under Construction" />
</body>
</html>
```
